sub_title: Creative Lead at Iridescence Studio Amsterdam | Cultural Researcher.
summary:
Self-starter, free spirit, creative, sharp and conceptual thinker, motivator, communicator, and an eternal believer in positive change through our united strengths.

Vast international experience in Amsterdam, Mexico City, Madrid and Croatia. Independent since 17, I managed to finance my education and needs, working while full-time studying and finding time and pleasure in voluntary work. Now I use that experience to empower teams and new projects. My work is based on lasting, quality based relationships. 

For the last 4 years I have designed successful content for people’s dreams and challenges by deeply understanding their vision. In 2017 I opened a design studio in Amsterdam and have since helped worldwide companies in positioning their messages. Working in the core design team of Learning Carpets for 2 years, I helped create educational material for children in Middle East, Europe and the Americas. My passion is creating a sustainable world with team work.

Let's connect and talk about our new project!
